Product name: Real Framed Butterfly Taxidermy Display F1562
Description:
This framed butterfly has a wavy brown and tan pattern with two submarginal eyespots.  It flies in the forests of Central and South America.  Professionally framed in a gallery shadowbox with Tru Vue UV blocking conservation glass -- a display built to museum standards.  
WHY UV BLOCKING GLASS IS IMPORTANT:
UV rays that come from all types of light degrade colors and specimens.  In order to preserve the beautiful colors and the specimen, it is important to have a frame with UV blocking glass.  Museums do this as well as all our framed insect displays.
comes with.......
- 6x6 Wood Shadowbox Display
- Vintage style museum card with natural history info.
- gift box
- information about the sustainable raising of insects.

Description:

SO in love with this Facial Serum not only will this facial serum balance hydration it will also stimulate regeneration.  Smoothing fine lines and wrinkles it is ultra luxurious! A master blend of some of the most therapeutic oils allowing you to achieve amazing facial results. This is the perfect oil to use year round but especially beneficial as the seasons change.  Consider this serum a facial tonic for the Skin promoting healing and balance.  This SERUM is extremely calming and soothing making this a PERFECT BEAUTY SLEEP OIL.  
So what are these amazing Powerful Oils and what do they do?
Of Course, Argan Oil (extremely nutrient rich in fatty acids and it. E)  
AND
Frankincense is a powerful astringent. It will also help lift and tighten. Bergamot a natural antibiotic and disinfectant to the skin that encourages healing while combating problematic skin. It is known for its use for fungal infections as well as reduction in the appearance of dark spots/hyper pigmentation.  Benzoin helps release nervous energy but also has amazing topical properties.  Rich in astringent properties and has been known to prevent bacterial growth and infection in wounds. Moroccan Blue Chamomile also know as Blue Tansy is a HERO in this Oil providing amazing medicinal power.  Deeply relaxing and soothing Blue Tansy is also a skin smoother, stress reliever and  is known to promote a feeling of self-control.  Known to relieve itching and its ability to calm the lymphatic system.  Yarrow is another HERO in this amazing Tonic. Yarrow has been used medicinally to treat a variety of pesky skin conditions and applied topically to promote healing.  Vetiver, Palmarosa and Petitgrain are all added to promote the healing and disappearance of scars fine lines and wrinkles.  Lets be real...love your laugh lines but the fine little lines from lack of hydration can most definetly disappear! 
 
SO WHY USE OIL???
Many are apprehensive about slathering on an oil. Especially when it comes to our face. So, here is how it works and why you should trade in your daily moisturizer for an oil treatment.
If you have oily skin the oil mimics the skins natural sebum (or oil secretion) and alerts your body to stop producing.  In dry skin the oil creates a protective but breathable barrier from free radicals causing dryness and helping to lock in moisture. If you have redness the oil helps with inflammation and soothes red irritated skin.  In blemished areas its helps to clean out and refresh pores..Using a small amount of this oil daily can work miracles for your face. I use it daily and I am very happy with my complexion. Keeping your face moisturized will help with fine lines and wrinkles. I also apply this oil to the lines on my forehead before I go to sleep. I have noticed a difference in their severity. 
You will receive a frosted glass bottle with a white dropper 1 fl oz.
This oil may be use daily and in the morning and in the evening. It is extremely calming and is recommended to use nightly as a Beauty Sleep Oil. This Oil is NOT to be consumed.

Product name: I Do Me Too Hand Stamped Forks with Custom Date • Stamped Silverware • Gift Idea for Bridal Shower
Description:
A perfect way to share your wedding cake, your first dinner as a married couple, or a special anniversary. You will receive 2 beautiful vintage forks hand stamped with "i do♥" and "me too♥"  and your special date on the handle.
The Details
All flatware used is vintage silverplate, ranging from 20 to 80 years old, that’s been upcycled to give it new life! I am very careful to select only table-ready silverware; however it may show some signs of wear. Please know that each piece is carefully handpicked by me and will be gorgeous but not brand new. 
Every piece is made to order, just for you. The flatware pattern you receive will vary depending on what is in the studio at the time of your order. I do source a wide assortment of styles, so if you have a personal preference (floral, simple, masculine, etc), please let me know in the “note to seller” at checkout and I will choose your perfect piece.
The Process
Hand stamping is a very different process than traditional engraving. Hand stamping is done entirely by hand, with a hammer and steel stamp. The stamps have letters or designs carved on the end and each is individually stamped into the metal with a hammer. Every item is carefully handcrafted, so certain variations are to be expected. This adds to the one of a kind nature and overall quality of each piece I create.
Please refer to shop announcement for current production time (this does not include shipping time).

GOLD-FILLED JEWELRY:
- Under normal wearing conditions and with proper care, your gold filled jewelry should last at least 10 years.
- 14kt Gold-Filled jewelry is made by bonding a solid layer of 14kt gold on top of another metal, but this layer is 1000 - 10,000 times thicker than gold plating, resulting in a durable, long-lasting product that looks gorgeous like solid gold.
- Gold-Filled jewelry can also be worn by people with sensitive skin.
STERLING SILVER:
- We use .925 Sterling Silver, which requires polishing from time to time from oxidation. You can easily restore silver back to shine with a polishing cloth or use a polishing lotion for that extra shine.

_______________________________
- PLEASE READ THE FOLLOWING BEFORE ORDERING - 
It is very important to READ ALL ITEM DESCRIPTIONS CAREFULLY. I make sure all my descriptions give you the information you need to make a purchase that is exactly what you want. Many customer questions can be answered by reading the item description. Each listing also includes several photos: close-ups for detail, photos on real life or life size models to see how it would look on and to give you a size ratio, photos of options for personalized items, and photos of how they are packaged. I always include dimensions and measurements of the various parts of each items so you know exactly what you’re getting. Lengths of necklaces will vary depending on the length you choose.
- PERSONALIZED ITEMS -
 
All my personalized jewelry offered here and on www.PamelaCurran.com is made to order and stamped by hand so it may vary slightly from what is pictured. Although great care is taken when stamping each piece, because the work is all done by hand, each letter may not be perfectly aligned with the others. This should not be considered a flaw but rather the characteristic of truly hand crafted jewelry. This type of craftsmanship makes no two pieces exactly alike - giving you the highly desirable one of a kind jewelry.
The process I use to oxidize the imprints on my sterling silver pieces is actually a professional chemical process that will not wear away. Some shops use ink (a Sharpie pen!) which is not permanent on metal. It is a quick and cheap way to darken the characters but doesn’t last. My process is an oxidation process that takes a little longer but looks better and will last for the lifetime of your piece.
Please note that my initial items are “hand stamped” – using pressure from a hammer to make the imprint. This will leave a slight visible sign on the reverse side so I won’t do stampings on both sides. Only an engraver, using a machine where the item is etched not hammered, should do double sided imprints.
If you would like more characters than the max amount offered in a listing, please contact me prior to ordering to see if it can be done and what the additional cost will be.
- FAQs (Frequently Asked Questions) - 
Below you will find questions I’m often asked, most of which are covered in my shop policies, but to make it easy for you I’ve listed the most commonly asked questions with their answers. 
Q:   What forms of payment do you accept?
A:  I accept all major credit cards and PayPal.
All payments are processed through PayPal but you don’t need a PayPal account to purchase from my shop, they just ensure your information remains safe.
Q:  When will my order be shipped?
A: All my designs are hand crafted – by me alone – and quality work takes time. You can find an estimated time frame on my shop home page but I always send confirmation emails giving you the current time frame before shipping. You can expedite the shipping  of your order by upgrading to EXPRESS shipping – but that will only reduce shipping time, not production time. If you need your item by a specific date, please contact me prior to ordering to see what can be done.
Q:   How long does shipping take?
A:  Standard shipping is via US Postal Service (USPS) 1st class mail and can take 3-5 business days.
You can upgrade to Priority Mail which will take 2-3 business days or EXPRESS shipping which is usually overnight but can take 2 days for some areas.
Q:  My order is a gift, can I have it shipped directly to the recipient?
A:  Absolutely! All you have to do is put the name and address of the recipient in the “ship to” section at checkout. Please do not write the shipping address as a “note to seller” at checkout – it means I will manually have to enter the alternate shipping address and can cause delays in getting your order. 
Q:  Do you have gift wrapping?
A:  All my jewelry offered here and on my website, www.PamelaCurran.com, is packed in either a cream colored gift box with white satin ribbon (neutral for any occasion) or a golden organza gift bag. Each listing shows a picture of the packaging for that item. If you are ordering items for yourself and are an eco-friendly shopper I will be happy to minimalize it to only protective packaging.  
Q:  Can I add a gift note with my order?
A: Of course! I can add a little personalized note for you with the jewelry, but please keep in mind the note card is only about a 2” square so keep your note brief! If it is too lengthy I will have to contact you about reducing its size and that may cause delays in getting your order shipped out.
Q:  What is 14kt gold filled?
A: Gold filled is NOT like plated gold (also known as vermeil or dipped gold). Plated pieces are made by using an electroplating process that will chip or wear away over a very short period of time – sometimes after only wearing the jewelry once or twice! They are sold at cheaper prices but aren’t worth it if you have to throw the jewelry away! Gold filled not only uses twice the amount of gold as plated, but uses a process of extreme heat and pressure to literally bond the gold to the underlying metal and if taken care of properly will give you several years of wear. Not all gold filled is 14kt – you can be assured I only use 14kt gold filled for my gold jewelry.
Q:  Do you use .925 silver?
A: All my silver designs are made completely of sterling silver, also known as .925 silver.
Q:  How do I care for my handcrafted jewelry?
A:  Sterling silver jewelry can be cleaned in warm soapy water and should be dried completely before wearing or storing. To dry it use a soft absorbent towel and either let air dry or if you’re in a very humid environment I recommend using a hair dryer to finish the drying process. It should be kept in either an anti-tarnish jewelry box or an air tight zip closure bag to prevent tarnishing. You can use a polishing cloth to remove any tarnish or if excessive you should take it to a professional jeweler.
14kt Gold filled, like solid gold, will darken when it gets dirty. All you need to do is gently wash your items in warm soapy water. I recommend something that rinses clean and doesn’t leave any film on your jewelry. Pat dry with a soft towel and let air dry completely before putting on or storing. You should keep your gold filled clean to maintain its brilliant gold color.
DO NOT swim or shower in your jewelry. Harsh chemicals and extreme heat can damage your precious metals, especially hot tubs are a big no-no. Also, showering in your jewelry doesn’t clean it – actually the opposite can be true. Beauty products like hair conditioner can build up on your jewelry causing it to get dirty more quickly. It only takes a few minutes to properly clean your jewelry and is worth it!
